rvisors a training survey administered to all employees and focus groups of employees with similar job responsibilities  The focus is currently policy and procedure  The program will expand as needs and interests change  Some topics will be  piloted  before being open to all of post  If you would like to participate in a pilot group  please let us know  Recent Topics  Evaluations Making the Required Useful Hire in Haste  Regret in Leisure Planning Successful Events at VMI Retirement Topics from VRS   TIAA CREF Nip It in the Bud  Progressive Discipline Alcohol and Other Drug Education Training Compensation Overview Americans with Disabilities Act Training Contact us at 540 464 7322 or sporerb vmi edu with suggestions for training topics  inclusion in a focus or pilot group  department specific training  or if you d like to present a topic yourself  Off Site Training Department of Human Resource Management Links to the current schedule of classroom offerings from DHRM  Commonwealth of Virginia Knowledge Center  Covkc  Links to current online course offerings from DHRM  You will need to register with this site  detailed registration instructions  Once you are registered  you have access to online courses as well as the schedule for courses offered around the state  Online courses of interest to all state employees are  Understanding   Using the Grievance Procedure Preventing Workplace Violence Communication Topics 22  Management Virginia  Topics OSHA and Other Safety Topics Leadership Topics Virginia Retirement System Education  VRS provides Retirement Education Seminars  RES    Group Counseling Services  GCS  at local community colleges  schedule  Please note that employees may attend these seminars without using leave time  so long as the absence is pre approved  VRS also provides additional information about retirement planning here  Local Opportunities Local businesses offer programs  many of them free  in their area of expertise  Here are some links to listings of