 Understanding   Using the Grievance Procedure Preventing Workplace Violence Communication Topics 22  Management Virginia  Topics OSHA and Other Safety Topics Leadership Topics Virginia Retirement System Education  VRS provides Retirement Education Seminars  RES    Group Counseling Services  GCS  at local community colleges  schedule  Please note that employees may attend these seminars without using leave time  so long as the absence is pre approved  VRS also provides additional information about retirement planning here  Local Opportunities Local businesses offer programs  many of them free  in their area of expertise  Here are some links to listings of these events  The News Gazette Lexington Visitor s Center   VMI Foundation Keydet Club Alumni Webcams Directories My VMI  RESOURCES   Title IX  Health   Safety   IT   Site Index Parents   Families   Cadets   Non discrimination Statement   Privacy   THE VMI PHILOSOPHY The VMI experience is framed by relevant education within a military environment  It s an education that develops character  fosters a lifelong appreciation of physical fitness engenders a sense of responsibility to others  and cultivates the ability to master adversity  VIRGINIA MILITARY INSTITUTE Lexington  Virginia 24450 General Information   540  464 7230  Admissions  admissions vmi edu HR Training Opportunities       HR Training Opportunities                     skip to content VMI VMI Foundation Keydet Club Alumni Webcams Directories My VMI Menu About About Us Administrative Offices Institute Report News  Photos  Videos VMI Archives Museums VMI Museum System The VMI Museum New Market Battlefield Stonewall Jackson House For Visitors Directions   Map Employment Parents   Family Conferences Chessie Nature Trail Bookstore Resources MyVMI Directories Friendly URLs Post View Health and Safety Computing Academics Areas of Study Majors   Minors Arts   Humanities Engineering Information   Social Sciences Life Sciences Natural Sciences ROTC Enrichment Inst